import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['start'] = pd.to_datetime(data['start'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['start'], bins=20)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of monarchs by their reign start year?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['start'] = pd.to_datetime(data['start'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data['end'] = pd.to_datetime(data['end'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data['length_of_reign'] = (data['end'] - data['start']).dt.days
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    ax.boxplot(data['length_of_reign'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average length of reign for monarchs in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.axvline(data['length_of_reign'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {data["length_of_reign"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['name'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the most common name among the monarchs in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['commonwealth'] = data['commonwealth'].astype(bool)
    commonwealth_count = data['commonwealth'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.pie(commonwealth_count, labels=['Not part of Commonwealth', 'Part of Commonwealth'], autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the proportion of monarchs who were part of the Commonwealth?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
